## Walker, Targeting & Looter Control
```lua
lua: Walker.SettingsChange("re walk delay", 200)
```
Change walk delay on the fly (lower = faster pathing).
```lua
lua: Walker.Enabled(false)
```
Stop the walker.
```lua
lua: Targeting.Enabled(false)
```
Stop attacking.
```lua
lua: Looter.Enabled(false)
```
Stop looting.
```lua
lua: if Walker.isStuck() then local m=Creature.iMonsters(3,false)[1] if m then Creature.Attack(m.id) end end
```
If stuck, attack the nearest monster to clear the path. *(See `state: targeting(if stuck)` for the native equivalent.)*

