## Native Walker Conditions & States
**Not Lua** — these are walker-config lines.

### Conditional `goto:` ( `goto: <label>, <condition>` )
```text
goto: ToSpawn, item(8309) >= 500
```
Jump to label if you hold 500+ of an item.
```text
goto: west, distance(32407, 32231, 10) > 2
```
Jump to label if more than 2 sqm from a tile — native arrival/retry check. _(test: confirm it respects floor)_
```text
goto: DepotRefill, item(8309) < 100
```
Route to refill when low.

> Condition functions usable in `goto:` lines: `item(id)`, `distance(x,y,z)`.

### `state:` toggles
```text
state: targeting(off)
state: targeting(on)
state: targeting(if stuck)
```
Targeting off, on, or **only attack when stuck** (native attack-to-unstick). _(test)_
```text
state: looter(off)
state: looter(on)
```
Toggle the looter (e.g. off while crossing a danger zone). _(test)_

